<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="356" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 MA/9–754: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName type="from">Dillon</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d356fn1">Repeated for
                            information to Manila.</note></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-07T20:00:00+01:00">September 7, 1954—8
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1005. Margerie<note n="2" xml:id="d356fn2">Roland Jacquin de Margerie, Deputy
                            Director General for Political and Economic Affairs at the Foreign
                            Ministry.</note> states Mendes has instructed La Chambre that French
                        delegation, except for suggesting verbal changes in draft, should go down
                        line with US on all major points.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dillon</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>